name: Alien Kill
overview: Alien Kill is a vertically scrolling shooter in which the player's objective is to kill as many aliens as he/she can. The game has the option for two-player co-op play. It was developed by David Farrar using Chris Yates' SEUCK engine in 1988. Published in ECP's "Gold Ribbon Game Pak".
publishers: ECP (Entertainment and Computer Products Pty. Ltd.)
